name: Sautéed Green Beans
briefdescription: Fresh green beans are sautéed in a skillet with a few seasonings, making a quick and easy side dish that pairs beautifully with any meal you're serving.
instructions: Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Add green beans, onion salt, garlic salt, garlic powder, and black pepper; cook and stir until desired tenderness is reached, 5 to 10 minutes.

comments.comment: Best. Green been. Recipe. Ever! I have made this for friends and family and they all love it.
